    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="83"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.00/344</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">William C. Bullitt</persName>, of
                        the Division of Western European Affairs, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                            of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-25">November 25,
                            1918</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Just as I concluded this
                        memorandum,<note n="7" xml:id="d83fn7">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> the appended telegrams were handed to me.<note n="8" xml:id="d83fn8">No
                        indication on file copy as to which telegrams these were.</note> They
                    confirm my fears and underscore my conclusions.</p>
                <p>I do not wish to be an alarmist but I feel that Bolshevism in North Germany is
                    inevitable unless we act at once and very wisely.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William C. Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
